Former Governor of Ekiti State and Leader of Peoples Democratic Party in the state, Ayodele Fayose has revealed why he dumped Professor Olusola Kolapo Eleka for Otunba Bisi Kolawole to become Governor this year.
Recall that Ayo Fayoseâ€™s preferred candidate, Otunba Bisi Kolawole who is a former member of the House of Assembly defeated Olusola Eleka and others in the recently conducted PDP primary.
Olusola Eleka, a former deputy Governor of Ekiti State was the PDP Governorship candidate in the 2018 Ekiti governorship election.View pictures in App save up to 80% data.
In a recent interview with The Punch newspaper, Fayose revealed that he dumped Olusola Kolapo Eleka for Otunba Bisi Kolawole not because the former deputy Governor is not fit to be Governor but it is just a matter of choice.

He added that his choice in 2018 was Olusola Eleka and now he is canvassing for Bisi Kolawole noting that he had nothing against the former deputy Governor.


